# Project Chimera

- **Before code:** Read root [`CLAUDE.md`](../../CLAUDE.md) and the relevant files under [`specs/`](../../specs/) (`_meta.md`, `functional.md`, `technical.md`, and `openclaw_integration.md` when networking applies).
- **DTOs:** Java `record` only for agent payloads; opaque blobs as JSON strings—never `Map<String, Object>` on DTOs.
- **External I/O:** Runtime integration only through MCP; no direct vendor HTTP/SDK calls from agent core packages.
- **Concurrency:** Prefer `Executors.newVirtualThreadPerTaskExecutor()` for worker-scale work; avoid raw `Thread` and legacy pools for swarm paths.
- **Tests:** JUnit 5; contract tests in `tests/` may be red until implementation—preserve or extend them instead of deleting to “go green.”
- **Traceability:** Public types need Javadoc tying to SRS sections and US-XXX where applicable.

For full wording, mirror policies in [`CLAUDE.md`](../../CLAUDE.md).
